I’ve been coming to Starbucks every single day for years. I just moved across the street making this location my new daily one. I understand that this location gets very busy, but even when I order on mobile order I wait 20-30 mins for my latte. It should not take this long to wait for one drink especially when you order ahead of time and a lot of times it’s not even made correctly. I’ve seen many other people angry and frustrated because it makes them late for work. This is the worst Starbucks I’ve ever been to and I think a lot of it has to do with a poor organization system. I’ve noticed the workers don’t call out the names on the mobile orders and the drinks are put in a spot where no one can reach over the counter and even see the names on it.  (There is one worker that knows who I am and always makes my drink quickly once I order. I wish he could work every day!)

I made an mobile order through the Starbucks app and went to go pick it up. I was waiting extremely long time to receive my order which is not uncommon in this location. Finally waiting 10 minutes to receive my order I realized I was missing cream cheese from my order. I brought it up to the attention to the barista named Kevin.  He said I didn't get cream cheese because I didn't pay for it and I told him I did because I made a mobile order. He told me that I didn't purchase the cream cheese and whatever purchases I made through the app is not his problem and I need to go wait in line like everyone else to buy the cream cheese in an overtly aggressive tone.  I went to the cashier and asked to speak with the supervisor on duty. The supervisor named Teresa approached me and asked me "what I needed assistance with". I told her on what just occurred with Kevin the barista and Keven proceeded to walk over where Teresa and I was having a conversation and he started to scream at me and tell me profanities. Teresa the supervisor did absolutely nothing to correct his behavior towards me, and proceeded to charge me for the cream cheese, that I already purchased via mobile order. When I finished making the purchase, and proceed to leave the store, Keven started tell scream at me and told me to leave and don't let the door hit you on your way out.  I am a frequent buyer at Starbucks and a Gold member and I have never experienced such disrespect in a Starbucks in my life.  I feel completely embarrassed and humiliated on the way I was spoken too and berated in front of other paying customers. I have been coming to this Starbucks for a year now and been a Starbucks customer over 4 years. After this encounter today I will no longer be a customer of Starbucks. I do not feel comfortable making any purchases from this location knowing how I was treated. I have a legit fear that Kevin or any of the baristas may purposely sabotage my future orders or speak to me the way Kevin, did once again.
